Further to my postings about the stupid centre clip used
by Kino on ASPHALT ... I had the pleasure of watching two
other Kinos over the weekend: the 2000 (?) version of
ROBIN HOOD, and the 2006 version of MABUSE.

Each of these three DVD's uses a different kind of centre
clip.  ASPHALT's is by far the worst -- I really had a
hell of a time wrenching it out of that box.

My question is, why does there seem to be no consistency
in the kind of centre clip Kino uses?  Are they so wealthy
(ha ha ha ha) that they can afford to hire somebody to
design a different clip for each release?

And in a slight segue here, how is the name "Mabuse"
pronounced?  I used to assume it was "Mah-byooz", but
now I'm wondering if it is "May-booz".

Graf von Galitzen, can you weigh in here, please?

Jim
